---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Mystery Box Poster"
  description="Privacy policy for the Mystery Box Poster app that publishes videos to the owner's own TikTok and YouTube accounts."
  type="website"
>
  <section class="page-intro">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>Last updated: June 21, 2026</p>
  </section>

  <article class="prose">
    <p>
      <strong>Mystery Box Poster</strong> ("the app") is a private tool used by its owner to
      publish their own short videos to their own social media accounts (TikTok and YouTube)
      through the platforms' official APIs. The app is not offered to the public and does not
      collect data from third-party users.
    </p>

    <h2>Information we access</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>OAuth access tokens</strong> for the owner's own TikTok and YouTube accounts,
        used only to upload and publish the owner's videos.
      </li>
      <li>
        Basic account info (e.g. display name) returned by the platform APIs, used only to
        confirm the correct account is connected.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How information is used</h2>
    <p>
      Tokens are used solely to upload video files and their captions to the owner's own
      accounts. We do not sell, share, or transfer any data to third parties.
    </p>

    <h2>Storage</h2>
    <p>
      Access tokens are stored locally on the owner's own computer and are never published.
      No user database or analytics service stores personal data on our behalf.
    </p>

    <h2>Data deletion</h2>
    <p>
      The owner can revoke access at any time from their TikTok or Google account settings,
      which immediately invalidates the stored tokens.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>For any questions about this policy, contact: thagvip1@gmail.com</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
